---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Ad Monetization Resources & Guides | AdBunny"
  description="Guides on remnant inventory monetization, banner ad optimization, and programmatic ad tech — from the team building AdBunny."
  keywords="remnant inventory guides, ad monetization resources, programmatic advertising blog"
>
<section class="page-header">
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Resources for Smarter Remnant Inventory Monetization</h1>
    <p>Guides, explainers, and updates on remnant inventory, banner ad optimization, and where AI fits into modern ad monetization — for publishers and demand partners alike.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-sm">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="grid-3">
      <div class="resource-card">
        <span class="tag">Guide</span>
        <h3>What Is Remnant Ad Inventory? A Practical Guide for Publishers</h3>
        <p>Understand remnant inventory, how it differs from premium inventory, and why it's a revenue opportunity most publishers leave on the table.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="resource-card">
        <span class="tag">Analysis</span>
        <h3>Waterfall vs. Real-Time Optimization: What's Actually Costing You Revenue</h3>
        <p>Why static waterfalls leave money behind and how real-time AI optimization changes the math for remnant inventory.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="resource-card">
        <span class="tag">How-To</span>
        <h3>How to Monetize Unsold Ad Space Without Adding Ad-Ops Work</h3>
        <p>A practical walkthrough for publishers looking to generate revenue from unsold inventory without growing their team or toolchain.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="resource-card">
        <span class="tag">Guide</span>
        <h3>A Publisher's Guide to Fill Rate: What's Normal, What's Not</h3>
        <p>Benchmark your fill rate against industry standards and learn where remnant inventory optimization can make the biggest difference.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="resource-card">
        <span class="tag">Explainer</span>
        <h3>Single-Tag Integrations: Why Ad Tech Is Finally Getting Simpler</h3>
        <p>How single-tag architectures are reducing engineering lift across ad tech and what that means for publisher monetization strategies.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
</BaseLayout>
